    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Martial Arts Handbook pg. 30</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 40 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 4 lbs</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d8 (small), 1d10 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> 19-20/x2; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P &amp; S; <strong>Special</strong> See text</p><p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Blades, Light</p><h3>Description</h3><p>Used in Avistan since before Earthfall, seaxes are straight, single-edged blades. The broken-back seax is the size of a short sword, and has a broad blade with a distinctive trapezoidal shape. If your Strength score is less than 15, you take a -2 penalty on attack rolls with a broken-back seax, as you're unable to put enough force into the blows to land them effectively.</p>"
